<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      p:only-child, span:only-child {
         background: #903C56;
         color: #f8f9f9;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> The <b>:only-child</b> CSS pseudo-class represents an element without any siblings. </p>
   
   <h3> Example #1: </h3>
   
   <div>
      <p> Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet. </p>
   </div>
   
   <div>
      <p> Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet. </p>
      <p> Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet. </p>
   </div>
   
   <h3> Example #2: </h3>
   <div>
      <p> Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet. </p>
   </div>
   
   <div>
      <p> <span>Lorem</span> ipsum dolor sit amet. </p>
      <p> Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet. </p>
   </div>
   
   <p> On the example above <b>&lt;span&gt;</b> element inside the <b>&lt;p&gt;</b> element gets selected because it's the only child element (has no sibling elements). </p>
</body>
</html>